      <hedline>
        <hl1>Can't Find a Parking Spot? Aww.</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What you failed to address are the hundreds of spaces that would be available on any given day had the drivers who take up two spaces been more considerate and parked closer to the car in front or behind them, or parked closer to the crosswalks.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What you failed to address are the hundreds of spaces that would be available on any given day had the drivers who take up two spaces been more considerate and parked closer to the car in front or behind them, or parked closer to the crosswalks.</p>
        <p>I place leaflets under their windshield wipers politely admonishing these drivers for taking up two spaces and asking them to be more considerate. I urge all the frustrated parkers to do the same.</p>
        <p>HOWARD KRONISH  Upper East Side</p>
      </block>
